description: The second week of spring break is under way with warmer weather and bigger crowds. Updated daily.

Alpha Tau Omega brothers revel in the surf and sand after their long journey to Pier Park from Troy, Ala. on Wednesday, March 13, 2013, in Panama City Beach, Fla. (Heather Leiphart | The News Herald)

Alpha Tau Omega senior Ethan Carroll leads the charge to the beach to mark the end of the twelve fraternity brothers' 150-mile hike from Troy, Ala. to Pier Park on Wednesday, March 13, 2013, in Panama City Beach, Fla. The men hiked more than 25 miles per day along US 231 to raise awareness and funds for the Special Olympics. The sand feels "so good," said Carroll. "It's so much better than 150 miles of concrete." (Heather Leiphart | The News Herald)

Alpha Tau Omega brother Miller Morrison greets friends Anna Ballard, left, and Slayton Scott upon arrival in Pier Park after a 140-mile journey from Troy, Ala. on Wednesday, March 13, 2013, in Panama City Beach, Fla. (Heather Leiphart | The News Herald)

Bay County Special Olympics athlete Justin Rigdon, center, leads other athletes and a dozen Alpha Tau Omega fraternity brothers in a cheer as they complete the final stretch of their journey to the beach at Pier Park on Wednesday, March 13, 2013, in Panama City Beach, Fla. The fraternity brothers hiked more than 25 miles per day along US 231 from Troy, Ala. to raise awareness and funds for the Special Olympics and were joined by Special Olympics athletes near Pier Park. (Heather Leiphart | The News Herald)
